hire, Scotland":"Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"cs":{"1340–1425":"1340–1425","1345–1409":"1345–1409","1375–1407":"1375–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Zesnulý","1425":"1425","before 30 June 1407":"před 30. června 1407","1345":"1345","1377":"1377","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1409":"1409","1407":"1407","Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland","Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"da":{"1340–1425":"1340–1425","1345–1409":"1345–1409","1375–1407":"1375–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Afdød","1425":"1425","before 30 June 1407":"før 30. juni 1407","1345":"1345","1377":"1377","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1409":"1409","1407":"1407","Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Craigie, Ayrshire, Skotland","Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Skotland","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Skotland","Scotland":"Skotland","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Skotland"},"nl":{"1340–1425":"1340–1425","1345–1409":"1345–1409","1375–1407":"1375–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Overleden","1425":"1425","before 30 June 1407":"vóór 30 juni 1407","1345":"1345","1377":"1377","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1409":"1409","1407":"1407","Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Craigie, Ayrshire, Schotland","Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Schotland","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Schotland","Scotland":"Schotland","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Schotland"},"en":{"1340–1425":"1340–1425","1345–1409":"1345–1409","1375–1407":"1375–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Deceased","1425":"1425","before 30 June 1407":"before 30 June 1407","1345":"1345","1377":"1377","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1409":"1409","1407":"1407","Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland","Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Douglas","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Scottish: habitational name from any of various places called from their situation on a river named with Gaelic <i>dubh</i> ‘dark, black’ + <i>glas</i> ‘stream’ (a derivative of <i>glas</i> ‘blue’). There are several localities in Scotland and Ireland so named, but the one from which the surname is derived in most if not all cases is Douglas in Lanarkshire 20 miles south of Glasgow, the original stronghold of the influential Douglas family and their retainers.","History: The family taking their name from Douglas in Lanarkshire were of Flemish origin. They rose to great prominence in the 14th and 15th centuries, controlling the earldoms of Douglas, Morton, and Angus, and later, Queensberry."],"variants":[{"name":"Douglass","meanings":["Scottish and English (Durham and Northumbria): variant of   Douglas  .","History: William Douglass, a physician recognized for his identification and description of an epidemic of scarlet fever, was born <i>c.</i> 1691 in Gifford, Haddington County, Scotland, and settled in Boston in 1718. The abolitionist, orator, and journalist Frederick Douglass assumed the name after escaping from slavery in 1838 and traveling to Massachusetts. Son of a white father and a slave with some Indian blood, he was born Frederick Augustus Washington Bailey <i>c.</i> 1817 in Tuckahoe, MD."]}]},{"name":"Margaret","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."],"variants":[{"name":"Margareta","meanings":["From the Latin form of Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>.  See  <b>Margaret</b>   ."]},{"name":"Margaretta","meanings":["An extremely common given name from the Middle Ages onwards, derived via Old French <i>Marguerite</i> and Latin <i>Margarita</i> from Greek <i>Margarītēs</i>, from <i>margaron</i> ‘pearl’, a word ultimately of Hebrew origin. The name was always understood to mean ‘pearl’ throughout the Middle Ages. The first  St Margaret  was martyred at Antioch in Pisidia during the persecution instigated by the  Emperor Diocletian  in the early 4th century. However, there is some doubt about her name, as the same saint is venerated in the Orthodox Church as   Marina .  There were several other saintly bearers of the name, including St Margaret of Scotland (  d. 1093 ), wife of  King Malcolm Canmore  and daughter of Edmund Ironside of England. It was also the name of the wife of  Henry VI  of England,  Margaret of Anjou  (  1430–82 ), and of  Margaret Tudor  (  1489–1541 ), sister of  Henry VIII , who married James IV of Scotland and ruled as regent there after his death.  See also  Margery  ,   Marjorie ."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"Margaret Douglas was born in 1340, in Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland. She married Sir John Wallace 7th of Riccarton in 1373, in Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland. They were the parents of at least 2 sons. She died in 1425, in Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland, at the age of 85."},"et":{"1340–1425":"1340–1425","1345–1409":"1345–1409","1375–1407":"1375–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Surnud","1425":"1425","before 30 June 1407":"enne 30. juunit 1407","1345":"1345","1377":"1377","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1409":"1409","1407":"1407","Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland","Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"fi":{"1340–1425":"1340–1425","1345–1409":"1345–1409","1375–1407":"1375–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Kuollut","1425":"1425","before 30 June 1407":"ennen vuotta 30. kesäkuuta 1407","1345":"1345","1377":"1377","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1409":"1409","1407":"1407","Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland","Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland":"Douglas Castle, Lanarkshire, Scotland","Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Paisley, Renfrewshire, Scotland","Scotland":"Scotland","Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland":"Eaglesham, Renfrewshire, Scotland"},"fr":{"1340–1425":"1340–1425","1345–1409":"1345–1409","1375–1407":"1375–1407","1377–Male":"1377–Décédé","1425":"1425","before 30 June 1407":"avant 30 juin 1407","1345":"1345","1377":"1377","1375":"1375","1340":"1340","1373":"1373","1409":"1409","1407":"1407","Craigie, Ayrshire, Scotland":"Craigie, Ayrs